          <q>The natural number  <m>n</m>  can be written as a sum of natural numbers, each of 
          which is a 2  or a  3.</q>
          Verify that
          <m>P( 4 ), P( 5 ), P( 6 )</m>, and <m>P( 7 )</m> are true.
          To use the Second Principle of Mathematical Induction, assume that 
          <m>k \in \mathbb{N}, k \geq 5</m> and that
          <m>P( 4 ), P( 5 ),  \ldots , P( k )</m> are true.  Then notice that
          <me>
            k + 1 = ( {k - 1} ) + 2
