          is a 2 or a 3.  Since <m>k + 1 = (k - 1) + 2</m>, we can conclude that <m>(k+1)</m> 
          can be written as a sum of natural numbers, each of which is a 2 or a 3. 
          This completes the proof of the inductive step.
